        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 4 at 3:47PM MDT by NWS Salt Lake City UT</headline>
        <description>At 346 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of La Verkin, or 15 miles west of Zion National Park.
This storm was nearly stationary.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Toquerville and Pintura.

This includes Interstate 15 between mile markers 28 and 36.
Localized ponding may occur on roadways.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
